It is important to determine the financial cost and the energy ratio associated with producing renewable diesel from algae. In general, the financial and energy costs should be directly related. However, the economics of energy production includes many variables that can skew this relationship [45, 46]. The energy required to produce renewable diesel (direct and indirect), ERD, in joules per liter, can be calculated as
