Based on the framework by Mulder and Hagens, the second-order energy return on investment for renewable diesel, EROIRD, can be defined as
15\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
