				\begin{document}$$ {\varphi_{{\text{se}}{{\text{p}}_{\text{UL}}}}} $$\end{document}, of Eq. 33. In a situation where a researcher may not have all of the above information, the results could be reported in symbolic notation. For instance, in a study by Richmond et al., Nannochloropsis salina was produced at a rate of 24.5 g/(m2-day) with a lipid fraction of about 16% in a pond with 0.12 m depth (cf. Sheehan et al. 1998, p. 191). This information translates to a triacylglycerol productivity that can be reported as
